{"id":43708,"title":"[Current approaches to the diagnosis and treatment for enteropathies].","abstract":"Enteropathies (EP) are the common name for pathological (inflammatory, hemorrhagic, erosive-ulcerative, and atrophic) changes in the small bowel. The paper describes the nosological entities of EP and the significance of laboratory and instrumental methods used for their diagnosis. It outlines the principles of etiotropic and pathogenetic therapies.","date":"2014-04-28","categories":"Digestive System Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24772500","annotations":[{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.75445,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Nosology","weight":0.747178,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nosology"},{"name":"Intestine","weight":0.728515,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intestine"},{"name":"Pathology","weight":0.718103,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathology"},{"name":"Inflammation","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inflammation"},{"name":"Pathogenesis","weight":0.70749,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathogenesis"},{"name":"Bleeding","weight":0.703547,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bleeding"},{"name":"Small intestine","weight":0.700396,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Small_intestine"},{"name":"Atrophy","weight":0.482562,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atrophy"},{"name":"Laboratory","weight":0.25769,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laboratory"},{"name":"Enteropathy","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enteropathy"},{"name":"Musical instrument","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Musical_instrument"},{"name":"Common name","weight":0.0158689,"wikipedia_article":"ht